  "prompt": "What is your most effective link building strategy in 2016?",
  "response": "In 2016, effective link building strategies focused on creating high-quality content and fostering genuine relationships to earn links rather than building them through manipulative tactics. Here are some key strategies that were effective during that time:\n\n1. **Content Creation and Promotion**: Producing valuable, shareable content such as blog posts, infographics, videos, and comprehensive guides that attract natural backlinks. Promoting this content through social media and outreach to influencers and bloggers can help increase visibility and link acquisition.\n\n2. **Guest Blogging**: Writing high-quality guest posts for reputable websites in your niche. This not only helps to build backlinks but also enhances your authority and visibility in your industry.\n\n3. **Broken Link Building**: Identifying broken links on websites relevant to your niche and offering your own content as a replacement. This helps webmasters fix broken links while providing you with valuable backlinks.\n\n4. **Resource Pages**: Finding resource pages in your industry and suggesting your content as an additional resource. Resource pages are curated lists of useful links, and getting listed can be a powerful way to earn backlinks.\n\n5. **Building Relationships**: Networking with influencers, bloggers, and industry leaders to build relationships that can lead to natural link acquisition. This can be done through social media engagement, attending industry events, and collaborating on projects.\n\n6. **Skyscraper Technique**: Identifying popular content within your niche and creating even better, more comprehensive content. Then, reaching out to those who linked to the original content and suggesting your improved version.\n\n7. **Competitor Analysis**: Analyzing your competitors' backlinks to identify potential link building opportunities. Tools like Ahrefs or SEMrush can help you uncover where competitors are getting their links from.\n\n8. **Internal Linking**: Improving internal linking within your own site to enhance the overall link structure and help search engines better understand your content.\n\nThese strategies focused on earning links through genuine value and relationship-building, aligning with Google's preference for natural, high-quality backlinks.",
